How can you implement a binary search algorithm in Java to search for an element in a sorted array? Can you provide a code snippet to get started?
Here is a sample Java code for binary search:
public class BinarySearch {
    int binarySearch(int arr[], int target) {
        int low = 0, high = arr.length - 1;
        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] == target)
                return mid;
            if (arr[mid] < target)
                low = mid + 1;
            else
                high = mid - 1;
        }
        return -1;
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        BinarySearch ob = new BinarySearch();
        int arr[] = { 2, 3, 4, 10, 40 };
        int target = 10;
        int result = ob.binarySearch(arr, target);
        if (result == -1)
            System.out.println("Element not present");
        else
            System.out.println("Element found at index " + result);
    }
} 
How would you modify this code to search for a target element in a larger array with 1000 elements?

output:
To modify the code to search for a target element in a larger array with 1000 elements, you would simply need to change the values of the array and target variable to match the new array. Here is an example:
```
public class BinarySearch {
    int binarySearch(int arr[], int target) {
        int low = 0, high = arr.length - 1;
        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            if (arr[mid] == target)
                return mid;
            if (arr[mid] < target)
                low = mid + 1;
            else
                high = mid - 1;
        }
        return -1;
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        BinarySearch ob = new BinarySearch();
        int arr[] = new int[1000];
        for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
            arr[i] = i;
        }
        int target = 500;
        int result = ob.binarySearch(arr, target);
        if (result == -1)
            System.out.println("Element not present");
        else
            System.out.println("Element found at index " + result);
    }
}
```
In this example, we create a new array with 1000 elements and assign each element a value from 0 to 999. We then set the target variable to 500 and call the binarySearch method to search for it in the array. The result will be the index of the target element if it is present in the array, or -1 if it is not.
